Huỳnh Anh Tú is an Intern/Fresher AI Engineer and Backend Developer with a strong foundation built through academic and personal projects. Their core expertise lies in Machine Learning, specifically advanced Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) techniques like Hybrid RAG and CRAG, leveraging Transformer architectures. They have practical experience in Backend Programming, Clean System Design, and developing user interfaces for both desktop (GUI) and mobile (Android) applications. Notable achievements include designing a Hybrid RAG system with Python, LangChain, Hugging Face Transformers, and PyTorch, incorporating web search and hallucination detection, and delivering a PyQt5 frontend demo. They also developed a mobile weather application with a Java Android frontend and Python FastAPI backend, integrating the OpenWeather API with offline caching and applying clean system design principles, alongside a Java GUI desktop application for a university system, implementing role-based login and MySQL integration.
Technically, they are proficient in programming languages such as Java, Python, Kotlin, and SQL. Their hands-on experience extends to frameworks and libraries including Spring Boot, PyTorch, TensorFlow, LangChain, FastAPI, Hugging Face Transformers, and PyQt5. They are skilled in database management with MySQL and SQLite, and possess domain knowledge in Android Development, API integration, and robust system design principles like role-based access, offline caching, and hallucination detection.